{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770053628,"nonce":"Z/JTw+ECswT5tx/ROjlKuvKjMDI=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87nsR0t","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/132","origin":"github"},"title":"[Architecture] Formalize workspace/project config separation pattern","message":"## Problem\n\nThe workspace is evolving a pattern where:\n- **Generic ROS 2 conventions** live in the root workspace (`.agent/`, `.github/instructions/`)\n- **Project11-specific details** live in individual project repositories\n\nThis pattern is emerging organically but isn't formalized. To make this workspace reusable for other ROS 2 projects, we need to document and enforce this separation.\n\n## Current State\n\n**Workspace-level (Generic ROS 2):**\n- `.agent/AI_RULES.md` - Core workflow rules\n- `.agent/knowledge/ros2_development_patterns.md` - ROS 2 package conventions\n- `.agent/knowledge/ros2_cli_best_practices.md` - ROS 2 runtime commands\n- `.github/instructions/ros2.instructions.md` - Generic ROS 2 guidance\n\n**Project-level (Project11-specific):**\n- Repository-specific conventions\n- Project-specific license requirements\n- Custom package configurations\n- Project-specific build requirements\n\n## Goal\n\nMake it possible to use this workspace with **any ROS 2 project** (not just Project11) without needing to clean out Project11-specific content.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n### 1. Document the Pattern\n\nCreate `.agent/ARCHITECTURE.md` (or update existing) with:\n- Clear separation of concerns\n- Guidelines for what goes where\n- How to adapt workspace for new projects\n\n### 2. Refactor Existing Content\n\n**Workspace-level should contain:**\n- ✅ ROS 2 conventions (colcon, vcstool, ament)\n- ✅ Git workflow rules\n- ✅ Testing patterns\n- ✅ Multi-distro support (Jazzy, Kilted, Rolling)\n- ❌ NO Project11-specific references\n- ❌ NO specific package names (helm_manager, mission_manager, etc.)\n\n**Project-level should contain:**\n- ✅ Project-specific package names\n- ✅ Project-specific license requirements\n- ✅ Custom dependencies\n- ✅ Project-specific workflows\n\n### 3. Create Template Structure\n\n```\n.agent/\n  ├── AI_RULES.md              # Generic workflow rules\n  ├── knowledge/\n  │   ├── ros2_*.md            # Generic ROS 2 patterns\n  │   └── workspace_*.md       # Workspace-specific patterns\n  └── templates/\n      └── new_project_setup.md # Guide for adapting to new project\n\nlayers/\n  └── \u003clayer\u003e/\n      └── \u003cworkspace\u003e/\n          └── src/\n              └── \u003cproject_repo\u003e/\n                  └── .github/\n                      └── copilot-instructions.md  # Project-specific\n```\n\n### 4. Example: Multi-Project Support\n\nAfter this refactor, you could:\n```bash\n# Use same workspace for different ROS 2 projects\ngit clone https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace.git\ncd ros2_agent_workspace\n\n# Option 1: Project11 (current)\n./scripts/setup_project.sh project11\n\n# Option 2: Different maritime robotics project\n./scripts/setup_project.sh marine_systems_lab\n\n# Option 3: Completely different domain\n./scripts/setup_project.sh autonomous_agriculture\n```\n\n## Benefits\n\n1. **Reusability** - Workspace can serve multiple ROS 2 projects\n2. **Maintainability** - Clear separation reduces confusion\n3. **Onboarding** - New projects can adopt workspace without baggage\n4. **Best Practices** - Generic ROS 2 patterns available to all\n\n## Tasks\n\n- [ ] Document current workspace/project split in ARCHITECTURE.md\n- [ ] Audit existing `.agent/` files for Project11-specific content\n- [ ] Move Project11-specific content to project repos\n- [ ] Create template for new project setup\n- [ ] Update agent instructions to respect this separation\n- [ ] Add validation/linting for this pattern\n\n## Priority\n\nMedium - Improves long-term maintainability and reusability\n\n## Related\n\n- Issue #131 - Licensing guidance (project-specific concern)\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: Copilot CLI Agent (Claude Sonnet 4.5)","files":null}]}